# Rule: General Icon Placement in Components

When adding an icon next to text inside any component (e.g., a link or a generic `div`), place the `<i>` tag and the text inside a container that aligns them, such as a flexbox. Use a `<span>` for the text to ensure proper spacing and styling.

## Example

This example shows how to add an icon to a SolidJS Router `<A>` component.

```tsx
// Example inside a link
import { A } from "@solidjs/router";

<A href="/profile" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2">
  <i class="modus-icons">user</i>
  <span>View Profile</span>
</A>;
```

### Modus Button Example

The same principle applies to Modus Web Components.

```tsx
// Example inside a Modus Button
<modus-wc-button color="primary">
  <i class="modus-icons">add</i>
  <span>Add Item</span>
</modus-wc-button>
```

### General Container Example

For any other container element, follow the same pattern:

```tsx
// Example with a generic div
<div class="flex items-center gap-2">
  <i class="modus-icons">settings</i>
  <span>Settings</span>
</div>
```
